# Smart Air Purifier — ESP32 BLE Controller

Aliou Tippett — Computer Engineering, University of Utah 2026

A BLE-controlled smart air purifier built on ESP32-S3 with a native iOS app. 
The ESP32 runs custom FreeRTOS firmware that controls a real air purifier fan motor via PWM and communicates wirelessly with an iPhone over BLE 5.0.

---

## Demo

Connect the iOS app, control fan speed, set a schedule, and watch the purifier respond in real time. 
Manual button presses on the original purifier hardware are detected and reflected in the app instantly.

---

## Features

- BLE 5.0 wireless control from iPhone
- Fan power on/off and speed control (Low / Medium / High)
- Real-time status notifications — app updates instantly on any state change
- Autonomous daily schedule — runs without phone connected
- Time-synchronized via iOS app on connect — no WiFi or cloud required
- Manual override via original purifier button board
- All inputs (BLE, schedule, manual) coexist cleanly via an event-driven architecture

---

## Tech Stack

MCU: ESP32-S3 N16R8 
Firmware Framework: ESP-IDF v5.5 
RTOS:  FreeRTOS 
BLE Stack: NimBLE
Build System: PlatformIO 

---

## Firmware Architecture

4 concurrent FreeRTOS tasks communicate via a central event queue:


BLE Task ──────────────┐
Scheduler Task ────────┤──► Control Queue ──► Control Task ──► PWM / GPIO
Manual Monitor Task ───┘


The control task is the single owner of all hardware. 
No other task touches GPIO or PWM directly — they send events and the control task decides what to do. 
This eliminates race conditions without needing hardware mutexes.

A mutex-protected purifier_status_t struct is the shared source of truth for all state.

---

\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\

## BLE GATT Service

Custom primary service with 6 characteristics:

Power (Write): On/Off 
Fan Speed (Write): Low / Medium / High 
Mode (Write): Placeholder for future modes 
Status (Notify): 9-byte real-time state push
Schedule (Write): 5-byte schedule payload 
Time (Write): 3-byte time sync from app 

Status notification payload (9 bytes):
```
[isPowered, fanSpeed, mode, scheduleEnabled, startHour, startMin, endHour, endMin, filterStatus]
```

