## Hardware

### Wiring Overview
```
ESP32-S3 (3.3V)
    │
    ├── GPIO 2 ──► Logic Converter CH1 ──► Fan PWM (5V)
    ├── GPIO 4 ──► Logic Converter CH2 ──► Fan Enable (5V)
    ├── GPIO 12 ◄── Logic Converter CH3 ◄── Button Board PWM (5V)
    └── GPIO xx ◄── Logic Converter CH4 ◄── Button Board Enable (5V)

Power:
    Purifier 5V rail ──► Logic Converter HV + Button Board VCC
    ESP32 USB / 5V pin ──► Onboard 3.3V regulator
    Common GND across all components
```

### Fan Control
LEDC peripheral, 5kHz, 8-bit resolution.
- Off: 0%
- Low: ~47% (duty 120)
- Medium: ~71% (duty 180)
- High: ~95% (duty 242)

### Button Board Input
Digital PWM at ~25kHz sampled at 47µs intervals (100 samples) to detect speed level. 
ISR detects edge change, task handles debounce and classification.

---

## Scheduler

The scheduler runs autonomously without BLE:
- App sends current time on connect (3 bytes: hour, minute, second)
- ESP increments internal clock every second
- Scheduler fires power on/off events at configured start/end times
- Supports overnight schedules (e.g. 10pm to 6am)
- Defaults to high speed when schedule turns on

